President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring March 25, 2015, as Greek Independence Day: A National Day of Celebration of Greek and American Democracy. The proclamation highlights the bond between the United States and Greece, rooted in common struggle and shared beliefs. It emphasizes the influence of Greek principles on America's founding and the inspiration drawn from Greek history and philosophy. The proclamation also recognizes the contributions of Greek Americans to the United States and expresses support for Greece's efforts towards long-term prosperity. The proclamation calls upon the people of the United States to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.